{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4c94ad55-a993-47bd-99a8-3b5799e1a65e","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `.csproj`** — Change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — Pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — Update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nThen run:\n```bash\ndotnet restore\ndotnet build\n```\n\nReview the [.NET 11 breaking changes](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/core/compatibility/11.0) and update any NuGet packages (e.g., `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0366ffd5-736c-444f-bfb0-5692c35d9b71","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET 10 ASP.NET Core web app to .NET 11. This is a straightforward question about upgrading .NET versions. I can answer this directly without needing to explore any codebase.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the three files they mentioned.","outputTokens":320,"requestId":"283C:38B4C:3524A4:3ED34B:69EAC9FB"},"id":"e953bb54-4ab8-4d71-9ef5-91366b9f809c","timestamp":"2026-04-24T01:40:19.602Z","parentId":"6a32a0e3-e1bc-4dad-80a4-5bbb73416f83"}
